# 1. 座長現る！

Emu: Everyooone! Morni-morni-good morning!!!
Emu: Let's do our best to make this another wonderhoy day!!!
Nene: Seriously, how it is possible for anyone to have so much energy in the morning...?
Rui: Good morning, Emu. Sounds like you're in an excellent mood again today.
Emu: Of course I am! Because today...
Emu: We get to start working with a new group!
Tsukasa: Yes, that's right...!
Tsukasa: I can't contain myself regarding the prospect of stepping onto a new stage! It even took me ten whole minutes to fall asleep last night...!
Nene: Wait, that sounds like a normal amount of time...
Rui: Hehe. In any case, I think it's safe to say that we're all excited about this opportunity.
Emu: Yeah! Having to say goodbye to everybody from Shunmeiza was kinda sad...
Emu: But I'm also really happy we got to learn so much from them!
Rui: Me as well. On top of having the privilege of performing in one of their plays, we were fortunate enough to help make a film. Both invaluable experiences by all accounts...
Nene: And they gave us such a nice send-off.
Tsukasa, Emu, Nene & Rui: Thank you very much for having us!
Shunmeiza Director: Yes, thank you for joining us. But it's sad to see you all have to go like this...
Shunmeiza Director: However, despite your short stay with us, you showed a tremendous amount of growth.
Shunmeiza Director: You in particular, Tenma.
Tsukasa: ...!
Shunmeiza Director: You still have a lot to learn... But your talent for truly becoming a character is unquestionable.
Shunmeiza Director: That will surely come in handy moving forward.
Tsukasa: Th-Thank you very much...!
Shunmeiza Director: For now, farewell. We'll be looking forward to seeing you all on stage again.
Tsukasa: Yes, and we can't thank you enough for everything!
Tsukasa: They were all such wonderful people...
Tsukasa: And I'm glad that we got to talk to Bakuno one last time.
Rui: It was nice of him to say that he hoped we'd get to perform together again someday.
Nene: That means we're all gonna have to get a lot better...
Tsukasa: Indeed! We'll need to learn as much as we can as we start working with Mikazukigumi today!
Emu: Yeah!
Emu: (That means I also have to do my best...!)
Emu: (I have to learn as much as I can about acting and how troupes work and stuff.)
Emu: (To make everyone in Phoenix Wonderland smile... To make everyone around the world smile!)
Tsukasa: Still, I have no idea what working with Mikazukigumi is going to involve...
Rui: They're known for putting on incredibly entertaining performances that are historical in nature.
Rui: They're particularly good at performing stunts and doing sword fights, so their practices may be very demanding physically.
Nene: Yikes, you're right... I'm gonna have to do my best to keep up.
Tsukasa: On the other hand, this is a golden opportunity for us to learn how to do stunts and sword fights!
Tsukasa: I had a chance to learn a little during a workshop a long time ago, so I'm very much looking forward to this!
Emu: Yeah, me too! I wanna go all, “Shing!” and, “Hiyah!” and stuff!
Emu: Oh, also...
Emu: I heard that the current leader of Mikazukigumi founded this troupe when he was still a university student!
Emu: So, I really wanna hear about how he actually founded this troupe and how he runs it!
Tsukasa: Ah, excellent! After all, acting is only a part of our training!
Emu: Hehe. I can't wait to meet him...
Delivery Person: Wh-Whoa!
Nene: Huh? What was that?
Tsukasa: Look, over there...! That delivery person on that hill...!
Delivery Person: Th-The dolly's getting away...!
Delivery Person: What if it hits someone?! Also, the packages are gonna get damaged!
Tsukasa: Th-This is bad...! We need to stop it!
???: Leave it to me!
Emu: Huh?
???: *Shout*
???: *Roar*
Nene: Wh-Whoa... He stopped the dolly. But it was going so fast...!
???: Phew. Okay, it's stopped...
Delivery Person: Th-Thank you very much! You're a lifesaver!
???: No, that's okay! It was nothing.
???: I was just putting my muscles to good use!
Tsukasa: No ordinary person would be able to do what he just did...
Nene: Y-Yeah... He's got an odd personality too...
Nene: But he seems really familiar...
???: Anyway, farewell! I have to be somewhere!
Emu: Oh, he's coming this way!
???: You guys are Wonderlands×Showtime, right...?!
Tsukasa: Y-Yes, we are. Does that mean you're...?
Kijima: I'm Daigo Kijima! Leader of the Mikazukigumi troupe!
Tsukasa: ...! We weren't expecting the troupe leader to come and meet with us first...!
Tsukasa: Please pardon us! My name is Tsukasa Tenma. Thank you very much for allowing us to work with your troupe so suddenly!
Kijima: Hah hah hah! There's no need to be so formal with me.
Kijima: Shosuke's told me all about how you're going around to train with different troupes.
Emu: What?! You know Shosuke?
Kijima: Hm? He didn't tell you?
Kijima: He and I attended the same university. We were studying different things, but met during this one class we both happened to be taking freshman year.
Kijima: I couldn't believe it when he came over and asked for my help. He said, “I need you to lend some people I know a hand. I beg you.”
Tsukasa: We had no idea...
Emu: Shosuke...
Emu: Umm... We look forward to working with you!
Emu: We want to learn as much as we possibly can to make our dreams come true!
Emu: We may end up causing you some trouble, but we're still going to do our best...!
Kijima: Yeah, of course!
Kijima: I'm not doing this because Shosuke asked me to. I'm doing this as a troupe leader and fellow actor. I'm here to help young talent such as yourselves grow.
Kijima: So, I'm prepared to give you all the support I can!
Emu: Mr. Kijima...
Emu: Hehe. Thank you very much!
Kijima: You're welcome! Now, follow me!
Nene: Huh?
Kijima: Time to run after that sun in the sky! After that, your training with Mikazukigumi will begin!
Rui: Look how far he's already gone.
Tsukasa: Wait, we're going to get left behind...! We need to start chasing after him...!
Nene: Wh-Why is running the first thing we're doing...?!
Rui: Hehe. Just think of it as a way for us to improve our stamina.
Tsukasa: Right... Which means our training has already begun! We should expect no less from Mikazukigumi...!
Emu: Hehe. Then, let's...
Emu: ...do our very best and have a wonderhoy time with our new friends!
Tsukasa: Yes, let's!
